SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The Organization has applied the provisions of ASC 740, Accounting for Uncertainty in Income Taxes. Under Accounting Standards Codification 740, nonpublic enterprises, including nonprofit organizations, are required to record a tax liability when substantial uncertainties exist as to whether certain income is exempt from federal, state, and local income tax. As of May 31, 2023, the Organization had no uncertain income tax positions.

The gaming activity listed in Part III is part of the annual event listed in Part II. The event as a whole retains $137,251 which offsets the raffle expenses as well as the Organization's charitable activities. For its fiscal year-end 2023, the Organization's program expenses were $475,200.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Evidence of enrollment is required to release funds to the institution. Operation School Bell provides new clothing and a backpack filled with school and hygiene supplies to students in the Orange Unified School District. Our OSB students are identified by local school administration as being in need of relief services. Special Assistance is provided based on referrals of economic distress.

OTHER PROGRAM SERVICES 4: Links to Learning provides scholarships to middle schools. Teachers and staff seeking new classroom learning experiences, enhanced art and music programs, or supplies for unique projects for their students apply for these grants. OTHER PROGRAM SERVICES 5: Special Assistance provides basic living necessities such as rent, utilities, and food to families in the City of Orange.
